Heat the oil in a medium size pan and saute corn and red onions until tender. Transfer corn mixture to a stainless bowl and add cut tomatoes and put aside. Mix olive oil, lime juice, SPLENDA(r) Granulated Sweetener, salt and basil in a small stainless bowl; toss with corn. Toss the shrimp, oil, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper in a small bowl. Cook shrimp on an open face grill for 2 minutes on one side and turn-over for an additional minute. Place cooked shrimps into corn salad mixture. Adjust seasoning and serve.